      {q:"Which asset typically has the highest long-term return?", choices:["Government bonds","Savings accounts","Stocks (equities)","Physical real estate"], correct:2, explain:"Stocks return ~10%/year historically (S&P 500). But short-term volatility is high. The reward for long-term risk-taking."},
      {q:"What is an asset's volatility?", choices:["Its tendency to always rise","The magnitude of its price fluctuations","Its dividend level","Its popularity with investors"], correct:1, explain:"Bitcoin can lose 50% in 3 months or gain 200% in 6. That's extreme volatility. Government bonds fluctuate little — low volatility."},
