      {q:"Why do high rates weigh on tech stocks?", choices:["Tech companies pay more taxes","Their future profits are worth less today when the discount rate is high","They can't borrow","Government regulates them more"], correct:1, explain:"Growth stocks derive most of their value from future profits. When rates rise, those future profits 'discounted' to present are worth less. Hence the tech crashes of 2022."},
